HEADWORD: drive-in window
<hw>drive-in window</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>a window at a business
establishment, such as a bank or restaurant, where patrons may transact
business or order goods while staying in their automobiles; <as>as, to
cash a check at the <ex>drive-in window</ex> of the bank</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

